The paper discusses the integrity and security of messages in vehicular ad-hoc networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of misbehavior detection mechanisms and subjective logic also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a generalized framework, which may involve software engineering (cs.SE) principles.
